<h3>Neighboring countries/oceans:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>On the southern border of the USA, Mexico is located right down below.</li>
        <li>On the northern border of the USA, Canada is located right above it.</li>
        <li>there’s contact with The Pacific Ocean to the west</li>
        <li> the Atlantic Ocean to the east</li>
        <li>the Gulf of Mexico to the southeast</li>
    </ul>
<h3>Capital</h3>
<p>The capital of the United States of America is Washington DC. It is located in the District of Columbia.</p>
<h3>States</h3>
<p>The United States of America has a total of 50 states. Getting a little bit deeper, there’s a total of 3,006 counties across the country.</p>
